  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b492ab769d202ee4183275be4bff9429, type: 3}
  m_Name: Laugh And Be Merry
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FlightPaper.ProjectSorrow.Poems.PoemScriptableObject
  id: 24
  title: Laugh And Be Merry
  author: John Masefield
  stanzas:
  - lines:
    - Laugh and be merry, remember, better the world with a song,
    - Better the world with a blow in the teeth of a wrong.
    - Laugh, for the time is brief, a thread the length of a span.
    - Laugh and be proud to belong to the old proud pageant of man.
  - lines:
    - 'Laugh and be merry: remember, in olden time.'
    - God made Heaven and Earth for joy He took in a rhyme,
    - Made them, and filled them full with the strong red wine of
    - His mirth
    - 'The splendid joy of the stars: the joy of the earth.'
  - lines:
    - So we must laugh and drink from the deep blue cup of the sky,
    - Join the jubilant song of the great stars sweeping by,
    - Laugh, and battle, and work, and drink of the wine outpoured
    - In the dear green earth, the sign of the joy of the Lord.
  - lines:
    - Laugh and be merry together, like brothers akin,
    - Guesting awhile in the rooms of a beautiful inn,
    - Glad till the dancing stops, and the lilt of the music ends.
    - Laugh till the game is played; and be you merry, my friends.
  rating: 2
